        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 5:26AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 524 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Lake Cisco to near Ranger. Movement was
north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Gunsight around 530 AM CDT.
Necessity and Lake Daniel around 535 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Morton Valley,
Nimrod, Staff, Scranton, Eolian, Olden, Harpersville, and Pleasant
Hill.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 324 and 357.
</description>
        <instruction>A severe thunderstorm warning will be issued soon for most locations
within this statement for a stronger storm near Rowden. Be certain
to monitor local radio stations and available television stations
for additional information and possible warnings from the National
Weather Service.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
